# Pages and routing (`apps/web/src/pages/`)

- **Layouts:** Prefer `BaseLayout`, `BlogLayout`, `TeamLayout`, `LegalLayout` from `apps/web/src/layouts/` instead of duplicating `<html>`/chrome.
- **Dynamic segments:** `[...slug]` is used for **`blog/posts`**, **`team`**, and **`legal`**. **`[tag]`** under `blog/tags/`. Match `getStaticPaths` to the same slug source as detail fetches.
- **Data source:** Listings and article-style routes load via **`sanityFetch`**, **`queries.ts`** string exports, and **`transformPost` / `transformTeamMember` / `transformLegalPage`** from `@/lib/sanity`. Avoid duplicating GROQ or fetch logic inline in pages.
- **Empty Sanity:** When `SANITY_PROJECT_ID` / `PUBLIC_SANITY_PROJECT_ID` are unset, `sanityFetch` can return **empty** — pages should stay consistent with that behavior (redirects to `/404` where already implemented).
- **RSS:** `rss.xml.js` uses the same Sanity post pipeline as blog pages; keep item `link` format in sync with post URLs (`/blog/posts/${slug}/`).
